			<div class="content" id="post-content-2471242">
									

<p>The first half of the writing was like night and day with the previous story. Which was day. It was flat and fast-paced, and I found myself dreading reading a long tale that wasn't holding up to your previous one.</p>
<p>Thankfully, the writing seemed to click once they started shooting the shit. Which of course makes me wonder if the first half was necessary. To be sure, I was kind of expecting part 2 to do more in-depth introducing of who's on Sigma-3 and what their mission is. Still, I like where this went, it's good to see Navarro in action, and I like the tie-in with Learning the Alphabet. That'll be fun. :)</p>

